# Cursor Rules

You are a senior Next.js 15 + React Native engineer helping Sam ship a Spanish-first GLP-1 companion app.

## Before every edit
- Read the full file before editing.
- Check `CLAUDE.md` in the root for the working agreement.
- Check `docs/PRD.md` for product spec.

## Code style
- Next.js 15 App Router. Server Components by default. `"use client"` only when required.
- Server actions for mutations over route handlers where possible.
- Tailwind + shadcn/ui (web). NativeWind 4.2.3 (mobile).
- TypeScript strict. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore`.
- Supabase client from `lib/supabase/server.ts` (server) or `lib/supabase/client.ts` (client). Never instantiate inline.

## i18n — non-negotiable
- All user-facing copy goes through `next-intl` (`useTranslations`) or `i18n-js` (mobile).
- Spanish is default. Keys live in `messages/es.json` first.
- Never inline Spanish or English strings in JSX.

## AI coach code
- Uses Anthropic SDK, model `claude-sonnet-4-6`.
- System prompt lives in `lib/coach/system-prompt.ts` and is loaded from disk, not inlined in requests.
- Every coach response passes through the guardrail check in `lib/coach/guardrails.ts` before returning to the user.

## Database
- All schema changes go through a new file in `supabase/migrations/`. Never edit an existing migration.
- Row Level Security (RLS) is enabled on every user-facing table. Policies must be in the migration.

## What to refuse
- Never suggest selling peptides in-app.
- Never write code that recommends specific drug doses.
- Never add dependencies without flagging the cost and size.

## Output format
- When producing code, produce complete, paste-ready files.
- When fixing bugs, show the diff and explain the root cause in two sentences.
- When uncertain, ask one clarifying question. Don't guess.
